author: Molly Blue | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Oregon Ducks defeat Washington Huskies: What they're saying
text:
Vernon Adams Jr . returned from injury and completed 14 of 25 passes for 272 yards and 2 touchdowns in Oregon's 26-20 win against the Washington Huskies in Seattle.
Social media offered a variety of responses to the outcome. Here's a sampling:
WATCH the Oregon-Washington Highlight #GoDucks http://t.co/a8x49zggE1
— CSNNW (@CSNNW) October 18, 2015
KEEP THE STREAK ALIVE! #CloseOne #ScoDucks
— Kwame Mitchell (@kwame_mitchell) October 18, 2015 The last time the Huskies beat the Ducks, neither Gmail nor Facebook existed. #GoDucks
— Chris Rifer (@ChrisRifer) October 18, 2015 All of ESPN'S GameDay analysts picked Washington to beat Oregon.
— Matt Prehm (@Prehmmr247) October 18, 2015 Hey @CharlesBarkIey what do you think of us now? https://t.co/UmdkrN7eJT
— Autzen Students (@AutzenStudents) October 18, 2015 Next year Oregon's winning streak vs Washington will be old enough for its Bar Mitzvah. #GoDucks
— Mike Jelline (@MikeJelline) October 18, 2015 haha pic.twitter.com/rrwWaIFhkE
— David Piper (@atqdave) October 18, 2015 It makes me feel good to hear the Ducks got the Win vs Washington #GoDucks
— Bo is for Boseko (@LOKOBOSEKO) October 18, 2015
